  "title": "Project Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Assist the Project / Site manager in project activities and progress, planning, implementation and monitoring work schedules in accordance to the master and detailed work programmes</li><li>Liaise with clients, consultants for technical issues, and coordinate the site activities with subcontractors</li><li>Ensure progress according to schedule, quality standards is maintained, site inspections are carried out and technical issues are resolved on time</li><li>Enforcement on authorities regulations and requirements</li><li>Co-ordinate, Program and monitor site work, material and workforce.</li><li>Resolve material and manpower issue as highlighted by subordinates.</li><li>Implementation of Cost / Quality control on site.</li><li>Plan, Lead and motivate workforce including supervision within the project</li><li>Ensure procedures, standards and guidelines are followed, maintained and implement corrective/preventive actions.</li><li>Able to produce working and As-Built drawing including O&M manual.</li></ul><p><strong>Job requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Able to carry out basic engineering design calculations</li><li>Well-versed in MS Office, MS Project, and AutoCAD</li><li>Strong interpersonal, communication and negotiation skills</li></ul>",
